verbose_text: The putative dipeptides that serve as cleavage sites, deduced by the similarity of the dipeptide alongside the upstream sequence using nepoviruses from subgroup B previously identified, were R 427 / A 428, R 617 / S 618, K 1212 / S 1213, R 1239 / S 1240, K 1449 / S 1450, producing the X1, X2, NTP, VPg, Pro and Pol proteins.
